## Sources

| Source | ID | Trust |
|--------|--------|------|
| PortSwigger Research | `portswigger` | ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ |
| Intigriti Blog | `intigriti` | ⭐⭐⭐⭐ |
| YesWeHack Blog | `yeswehack` | ⭐⭐⭐⭐ |
| Medium — Bug Bounty Writeups | `medium_wu` | ⭐⭐⭐⭐ |
| Medium — Bug Bounty | `medium_bb` | ⭐⭐⭐ |
| DEV Community | `devto` | ⭐⭐⭐ |
| GitHub Bug Bounty Writeups | `github_wu` | ⭐⭐⭐ |

---

## Example Configuration

```jsonc
{
  "discord_webhook": "...",

  "schedule": {
    "loop": true,
    "interval_minutes": 60,
    "items_per_run": 1
  },

  "sources": [
    {
      "id": "portswigger",
      "enabled": true,
      "weight": 5
    }
  ]
}
```

---

## Cron

```cron
# Every hour
0 * * * * cd /path/to/bitthewriteup && python3 bitthewriteup.py --once >> cron.log 2>&1

# Daily summary
0 21 * * * cd /path/to/bitthewriteup && python3 bitthewriteup.py --summary >> cron.log 2>&1
```

---

## Adding a Source

```python
{
    "name": "Example Blog",
    "id": "example",
    "type": "rss",
    "weight": 3,
    "url": "https://example.com/feed",
}
```

Enable it in `config.json`:

```json
{
    "id": "example",
    "enabled": true,
    "weight": 3
}
```

---

## Project Structure

| File | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `bitthewriteup.py` | Main script |
| `config.json` | User configuration |
| `queue.json` | Prioritized queue |
| `sent.log` | Duplicate prevention |
| `run.log` | Runtime logs |

